                <p class="content-lg font-weight-light">
                    Mian Ali is a Serial Entrepreneur and Investor who founded his first company TransData in 2003 providing support and IT services to businesses around the globe that now employs 400+ employees, and serves Fortune500 customers. He then founded TransCure in 2011, now at 250 employees with a focus on the US healthcare sector.
                </p>
                <p class="content-lg font-weight-light">
                    An angel investor, Mian Ali has invested in 15 startups from the US, Jamaica, to the UK and Finland. He is currently focused on his Incubator and Accelerator based in Lahore, Pakistan.
                </p>
                <p class="content-lg font-weight-light">
                    Mian also oversees IRS Foundation which is a non-profit organization he founded in 2009, actively working on education, poverty alleviation and primary healthcare for underprivileged sections of the population.
                </p>
                <p class="content-lg font-weight-light">
                    Mian is a General Partner at Markhor Capital and is dedicated to driving the development of the Pakistani start-up ecosystem.
                </p>
