                <p class="content-lg font-weight-light">
                    Syed is a lateral thinking serial entrepreneur with a strong background in Technology, Investment Banking and Corporate Development. The youngest elected Director in the history of the UK Pakistan Chamber of Commerce and driving the 2019 delegation to Pakistan; Syed is a trusted resource at the intersection of venture development, finance and technology and a recognised voice with both the Governments of the United Kingdom and Pakistan. On the invitation of the Special Assistant to the Prime Minister Sayed Zulfiqar Bukhari, Syed was asked to inspect Pakistan’s national start-up ecosystem at NUST to advise on developing ecosystems. Syed is also involved as a diplomat; HRH Prince William's visit to Pakistan in 2019, and successfully lobbied for direct COVID-19 repatriation flights in with the UK First Secretary of State The Rt Hon Dominic Raab MP.
                </p>
                <p class="content-lg font-weight-light">
                    Syed is currently the Managing Director of General Western and CEO of Firnas Private; a UK Aviation company.
                </p>
                <p class="content-lg font-weight-light">
                    Syed is a General Partner at Markhor Capital and is passionate about developing communities through commerce
                </p>
